1	Designful Leadership I 3-day Foundational JULY 2016 ( 6, 7 and 8 July 2016 )	<p>3-day Experiential Training on:<br />\r\nLeading Change, Being Effective and Creating True Impact in life and work, through Design Thinking and Mindful Leadership.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>The world is transforming.&nbsp;</em></strong>And in Cambodia, rapid modernization and development adds to this change. It&rsquo;s dizzying.&nbsp;<em>How do we lead effectively in the time of such changes?</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="/static/upload/201607221706232364.jpg" style="float:left; height:300px; margin:10px; width:225px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Mindfulness</strong>&nbsp;can dramatically improve our productivity. The teachings and practices of the old masters are directly applicable to the new environment, and the new style of management that&rsquo;s emerging.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The changes around us also require our frame of mind to change.<strong>Design Thinking&nbsp;</strong>is a tool that&rsquo;s perfectly fit for solving today&rsquo;s most difficult problems. Many organizations are adopting this framework, in their trainings, product development processes, and marketing strategies.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>AND,&nbsp;<strong>Design Thinking</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>Mindful Leadership</strong>&nbsp;have more than a few things in common: focus on the&nbsp;<strong>human experiences, empathy</strong>, and&nbsp;<strong>awareness&nbsp;</strong>are the foundation&nbsp;skills, used in both. The two frameworks can reinforce and deepen the understanding of each other.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="/static/upload/201607221706582490.jpg" style="float:left; height:180px; margin:10px; width:250px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;This experiential, hands-on workshop&nbsp;</strong>will equip you with a set of skills &nbsp;immediately &nbsp;applicable to making your work more effective and meaningful today.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;The participants will engage in&nbsp;<strong>more than eight (8) team exercises</strong>throughout &nbsp;the&nbsp;<strong>two and &nbsp;half day</strong>, putting into practice what they learn right there and then. They &nbsp;will receive a &nbsp;workbook with templates and instructions for conducting these exercises &nbsp;themselves.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>LEARN HOW TO</h2>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n\t<li><strong>Design a User-Centered Solution</strong>s to people&rsquo;s Problems, rather than a tried-and-failed attempts that are just enough to keep your job.</li>\r\n\t<li><strong>&ldquo;Fire Up&rdquo; a team to make a big difference</strong>&nbsp;through participatory idea-generation exercises</li>\r\n\t<li><strong>Gain control over your mind, and focus your energy</strong>&nbsp;more effectively</li>\r\n\t<li><strong>Inspire</strong>, not &ldquo;manage,&rdquo;&nbsp;<strong>your team through mindfulness, compassion and self-leadership</strong></li>\r\n\t<li><strong>Cultivate&nbsp;</strong>your own&nbsp;<strong>Creative Confidence</strong>, so your team can cultivate theirs</li>\r\n\t<li><strong>Share your vision,&nbsp;</strong>communicate effectively and mediate workplace conflicts</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>WHO SHOULD ATTEND</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li>leaders</li>\r\n\t<li>communication professionals</li>\r\n\t<li>managers</li>\r\n\t<li>program/project managers</li>\r\n\t<li>trainers</li>\r\n\t<li>&hellip;and anyone who wants to be more effective at his/her work!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>OUTLINE</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>Module I: OPEN WILL</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n\t<li>Power of Focus&mdash;meditation, or &ldquo;Attentional Training&rdquo; for your work</li>\r\n\t<li>Develop Mentality of Commitment and True Confidence</li>\r\n\t<li>7 Factors of Mindful Leadership</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>Module II: OPEN MIND</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n\t<li>Design Thinking and Open Mind</li>\r\n\t<li>What are we working on? Clarity at the Start</li>\r\n\t<li>Insights: Collect Observations and Ideas</li>\r\n\t<li>Prototype: Make Quickly, Test to&nbsp;Learn</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>Module III: OPEN HEART</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n\t<li>Deep Listening</li>\r\n\t<li>Facilitation for Understanding</li>\r\n\t<li>Putting it All Together</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>Please contact Chhunny if you want more information @&nbsp;<a href="mailto:chhuny@anakot.asia">chhunny@anakot.asia</a>&nbsp;| mobile : 078785044</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>ABOUT THE FACILITATORS:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="/static/upload/201607221707204400.jpg" style="float:left; height:150px; margin:10px; width:150px" /><strong>&nbsp; Akira MORITA</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;is a founder of Design Kompany, design and strategy consultancy with clients in North &nbsp;America, Europe and Asia. DK has helped hundreds of fellow small businesses and organizations infuse &nbsp;creativity in their work so they can innovate and grow.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;He is a passionate advocate of open collaborations between sectors and disciplines. His current involvement with &nbsp;Cambodian design and development sectors include: consultancy at Development Innovations, a USAID-funded i &nbsp;nitiative; mentorship at Impact HUB Phnom Penh, a social enterprise venture; and founding member of Design &nbsp;Phnom Penh, a local initiative of Cambodia&rsquo;s design curious and practitioners.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>His experience working with clients large and small over his 10-year career has trained him to be an effective communicator of methods, principles and practice of human centered design, strategic planning and creative thinking. He holds a M.S. in Parks, Recreation and Tourism Management from North Carolina State University.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="/static/upload/201607221707381860.jpg" style="float:left; height:150px; margin:10px; width:150px" /><strong>&nbsp;Chhunny NOEM</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;has over twelve years of experience in leadership, management, group dynamics, public &nbsp; &nbsp;speaking, training and motivational speaking.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;He prides himself on providing relevant and interactive learning forums where participants feel both comfortable to &nbsp;share, yet challenged to question their existing assumptions. Chhunny adds-value to participants&rsquo; learning by &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; weaving personal wellness and balance into every training program he offers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;Chhunny is a co-founder of Smallworld Cambodia, and a former co-Director of Possibilities World, a training &nbsp;company delivering Leadership Development and Management solutions. Chhunny has also delivered training workshops for clients in both the private and NGO sectors in leadership, management, soft skills and customer service. These clients include: a+b=3, 17 Triggers, Amansara Resort, Artisans D&rsquo;Angkor, Ucare Pharmacy, Shinta Mani Hotel, Soria Moria Hotel, Tara Angkor Hotel, Rambutan Resort, Clear Cambodia, ICS Asia, Phare Cambodia Circus, Young Startup Cambodia, CEFY project, Mlob Tapang and Farm to Table restaurant.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Chhunny taught meditation at the International Meditation Center of Chiang Mai for several years, incorporating the tenets of leadership and meditation as a guide for people on their quest towards effective self-empowerment, self-belief, and determination, and equipping them with the tools to create safe environments around them while committing to their life&rsquo;s passion.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Currently, he is a founding director of&nbsp;<a href="http://anakot.asia/" target="_blank">Anakot Asia</a>, a social enterprise that catalyzes the potential in human transformation and development through innovative training solutions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>WHERE:&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Intercontinental Hotel, Phnom Penh:&nbsp;</strong>296, Mao Tse Toung Blvd. (245), Phnom Penh 12306</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>WHEN:&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>July 6, 7, 8 (9 AM &ndash; 5 PM)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>PRICE:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>$295 per person, including three (3)&nbsp;lunches, refreshments, worksheets, a folder &amp; a certificate upon completion.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><em><strong>Register Today! Early-bird Registration (with $45 discount!) until June&nbsp;20</strong></em></h2>\r\n	data:image/jpeg;base64,	designful-leadership-i-3-day-foundational-july-2016-6-7-and-8-july-2016	5	1	3 days	45	Intercontinental Hotel, Phnom Penh: 296, Mao Tse Toung Blvd. (245), Phnom Penh 12306		2016-07-22 16:57:33.497587	2
2	Building Team Spirit: a four-hour intensive (January 30, 2016)	<h2>1/2 Day Workshop on Effective Communication Skills</h2>\r\n\r\n<h2>1 &ndash; 5 PM, SiSCO Cafe, BKK1</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="/static/upload/201607221712135478.jpg" style="float:left; height:200px; margin:10px; width:300px" /><em>&nbsp;Working together as a team well is one of the most essential professional skills, and &nbsp;the biggest asset to your organization</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;Do you work with a team? Of course you do. Does your team work as well as it could? Do you wonder what it would take to build a team that succeeds together?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ANAKOT and its team of trainers&mdash;a creative team with background in meditation, leadership and communication, innovation and design, acting and marketing&mdash;will teach you various activities and exercises that you can take back to your workplace to start building your own dream team, today.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You will engage in hands-on, practical exercises designed to heighten the sense of your level of communication skills, and how you might work on improving them. You will learn your strengths and weaknesses, and how to take advantage of them in your communication with others. You will come away with a set of practices that you can easily continue on your own, and a set of resources to further your learning.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>LEARN HOW TO:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n\t<li><strong>Lead a team without micro-managing</strong>: know different personality&nbsp;styles&nbsp;can work together well by listening to and accepting each other</li>\r\n\t<li><strong>How to listen, plan and execute as a group</strong>&nbsp;toward common goals</li>\r\n\t<li><strong>Harvest energy and ideas&nbsp;from your team&nbsp;</strong>without&nbsp;boring them with a formal meeting</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>WHO SHOULD ATTEND:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li>leaders</li>\r\n\t<li>communication professionals</li>\r\n\t<li>managers</li>\r\n\t<li>program/project managers</li>\r\n\t<li>trainers</li>\r\n\t<li>&hellip;and anyone who wants to be more effective at his/her work!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>OUTLINE:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Module I:&nbsp;Your Leadership Style</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n\t<li>Know Your Color</li>\r\n\t<li>Diversity as Strength</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Module II: Strategies for Success</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n\t<li>Five Dysfunctions of a Team</li>\r\n\t<li>Openness: Antidote to Fear</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Module III:&nbsp;Managing Challenges</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n\t<li>Team Challenge Games</li>\r\n\t<li>Putting it all together</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>Please contact Chhunny if you want more information @&nbsp;<a href="mailto:chhuny@anakot.asia">chhunny@anakot.asia</a>&nbsp;| mobile : 078785044</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>ABOUT THE FACILITATORS:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="/static/upload/201607221712498809.jpg" style="float:left; height:150px; margin:10px; width:150px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Akira MORITA</strong>&nbsp;is a principal of Design Kompany, creative guru at Anakot and a listening enthusiast. He brings his thoughtful, design-centered ideas about work, creativity and collaborative innovation into the world of professional training.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://phnompenh.impacthub.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/163/2015/08/Chunny.jpg"><img alt="Chunny" src="/static/upload/201607221713056869.jpg" style="border-style:solid; border-width:1px; float:left; height:150px; margin:10px; width:150px" /></a><strong>Chhunny NOEM</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;has over twelve years of experience in leadership, management, group dynamics, public speaking, training and motivational speaking.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He prides himself on providing relevant and interactive learning forums where participants feel both comfortable to share, yet challenged to question their existing assumptions. Chhunny adds-value to par