7	Designful Leadership Foundation I 2 1/2-day Course January 2016 ( 6-7 and 8 January 2016 )	<p>2 &frac12;-day Experiential Workshop on:<br />\r\n&mdash;Creating Change, Being Effective and Getting S**t Done in life and work, through&nbsp;Design Thinking and Mindful Leadership</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>What is Designful Leadership?</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>The world is transforming.&nbsp;</em></strong>And in Cambodia, rapid modernization and development adds to this change. It&rsquo;s dizzying.&nbsp;<em>How do we lead effectively when everyone is distracted by all the changes and Facebook feeds? How do we ourselves keep ourselves focused when there&rsquo;s 200 emails to attend to every day?</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="mindful people 2" src="/static/upload/201607221748547773.jpg" style="float:left; height:300px; margin:10px; width:225px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Meditation&nbsp;</strong>practice,&nbsp;<strong>mindfulness&nbsp;</strong>can dramatically improve our productivity. The teachings of the old masters are directly applicable to the new environment, and the new style of management that&rsquo;s emerging.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The changes around us also require our frame of mind to change.<strong>Design Thinking&nbsp;</strong>is a tool that&rsquo;s perfectly fit for solving today&rsquo;s most difficult problems. Many organizations are adopting methods based on this framework, in their training, product development processes, and marketing strategies.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Design Thinking</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>Mindful Leadership</strong>&nbsp;have more than a few things in common: focus on the<strong>human experiences, empathy</strong>, and&nbsp;<strong>awareness&nbsp;</strong>are the foundation&nbsp;skills used in both and reinforce principles of each other.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="mindful people" src="/static/upload/201607221749132094.jpg" style="float:left; height:187px; margin:10px; width:250px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>This experiential, hands-on workshop&nbsp;</strong>will equip you with a set of skills immediately applicable to making your work more effective and meaningful today.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The participants will engage in&nbsp;<strong>more than eight (8) team exercises</strong>throughout the&nbsp;<strong>two and half day</strong>, putting into practice what they learn right there and then. They will receive a workbook with templates and instructions for conducting these exercises themselves.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>LEARN HOW TO:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n\t<li><strong>Design a User-Centered Solution</strong>s to people&rsquo;s Problems, rather than a tried-and-failed attempts that are just enough to keep your job.</li>\r\n\t<li><strong>&ldquo;Fire Up&rdquo; a team to make a big difference</strong>&nbsp;through participatory idea-generation exercises</li>\r\n\t<li><strong>Gain control over your mind, and focus your energy</strong>&nbsp;more effectively</li>\r\n\t<li><strong>Inspire</strong>, not &ldquo;manage,&rdquo;&nbsp;<strong>your team through mindfulness, compassion and self-leadership</strong></li>\r\n\t<li><strong>Cultivate&nbsp;</strong>your own&nbsp;<strong>Creative Confidence</strong>, so your team can cultivate theirs</li>\r\n\t<li><strong>Share your vision,&nbsp;</strong>communicate effectively and mediate workplace conflicts</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>WHO SHOULD ATTEND:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li>leaders</li>\r\n\t<li>communication professionals</li>\r\n\t<li>managers</li>\r\n\t<li>program/project managers</li>\r\n\t<li>trainers</li>\r\n\t<li>&hellip;and anyone who wants to be more effective at his/her work!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>OUTLINE:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Module 0: Meditation, or &ldquo;Attentional Training&rdquo; for your work</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n\t<li>power of focus</li>\r\n\t<li>develop mental attitude</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Module I: 7 Factors of Mindful Leadership</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n\t<li>Be an Excellent Role Model</li>\r\n\t<li>Be Confident and Committed</li>\r\n\t<li>Value Clarity in Decision Making</li>\r\n\t<li>Be Adaptable &amp; Humble</li>\r\n\t<li>Start with Compassion</li>\r\n\t<li>Open to Change &amp; Innovations</li>\r\n\t<li>Wisdom in Action</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Module II: Design Thinking as a Framework</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n\t<li>Vision: What is the problem?</li>\r\n\t<li>Insights: Collect observations and ideas</li>\r\n\t<li>Prototype: Make quickly, test to&nbsp;learn</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Module III: Mindful Design&ndash;combining the two disciplines</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Please contact Chhunny if you want more information @&nbsp;<a href="mailto:chhuny@anakot.asia">chhunny@anakot.asia</a>&nbsp;| mobile : 078785044</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>ABOUT THE FACILITATORS:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="am-mug" src="/static/upload/201607221749406899.jpg" style="float:left; height:150px; margin:10px; width:150px" /><strong>Akira MORITA</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;is a founder of Design Kompany, design and strategy consultancy with clients in North America, Europe and Asia. DK has helped hundreds of fellow small businesses and organizations infuse creativity in their work so they can innovate and grow.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He is a passionate advocate of open collaborations between sectors and disciplines. His current involvement with Cambodian design and development sectors include: consultancy at Development Innovations, a USAID-funded initiative; mentorship at Impact HUB Phnom Penh, a social enterprise venture; and founding member of Design Phnom Penh, a local initiative of Cambodia&rsquo;s design curious and practitioners.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>His experience working with clients large and small over his 10-year career has trained him to be an effective communicator of methods, principles and practice of human centered design, strategic planning and creative thinking. He holds a M.S. in Parks, Recreation and Tourism Management from North Carolina State University.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://phnompenh.impacthub.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/163/2015/08/Chunny.jpg"><img alt="Chunny" src="/static/upload/201607221749579467.jpg" style="float:left; height:150px; margin:10px; width:150px" /></a>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>Chhunny NOEM</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;has over twelve years of experience in leadership, management, group dynamics, public speaking, training and motivational speaking.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He prides himself on providing relevant and interactive learning forums where participants feel both comfortable to share, yet challenged to question their existing assumptions. Chhunny adds-value to participants&rsquo; learning by weaving personal wellness and balance into every training program he offers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Chhunny is a co-founder of Smallworld Cambodia, and a former co-Director of Possibilities World, a training company delivering Leadership Development and Management solutions. Chhunny has also delivered training workshops for clients in both the private and NGO sectors in leadership, management, soft skills and customer service. These clients include: a+b=3, 17 Triggers, Amansara Resort, Artisans D&rsquo;Angkor, Ucare Pharmacy, Shinta Mani Hotel, Soria Moria Hotel, Tara Angkor Hotel, Rambutan Resort, Clear Cambodia, ICS Asia, Phare Cambodia Circus, Young Startup Cambodia, CEFY project, Mlob Tapang and Farm to Table restaurant.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Chhunny taught meditation at the International Meditation Center of Chiang Mai for several years, incorporating the tenets of leadership and meditation as a guide for people on their quest towards effective self-empowerment, self-belief, and determination, and equipping them with the tools to create safe environments around them while committing to their life&rsquo;s passion.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Currently, he is a founding director of&nbsp;<a href="http://anakot.asia/" target="_blank">Anakot Asia</a>, a social enterprise that catalyzes the potential in human transformation and development through innovative training solutions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>WHERE:&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>SiSCO Cafe:&nbsp;</strong>Street 51 (Pasteur) &amp; Street 370</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>WHEN:&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>January&nbsp;6, 7 (9 AM &ndash; 5 PM), and 8 (9 AM &ndash; 12 noon)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>PRICE:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>$291 per person, including three (3)&nbsp;lunches, refreshments, worksheets, a folder &amp; a certificate upon completion.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><em><strong>Register Today! Registration closes on Jan. 5</strong></em></h2>\r\n	data:image/jpeg;base64,	designful-leadership-foundation-i-2-12-day-course-january-2016-6-7-and-8-january-2016	6	1	2 ½-day	291	SiSCO Cafe: Street 51 (Pasteur) &amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp; Street 370		2016-07-22 17:51:06.232036	5
6	Communication for Success: a four-hour intensive ( January 29, 2016 )	<p>1/2 Day Workshop on Effective Communication Skills</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="/static/upload/201607221744094709.jpg" style="float:left; height:300px; margin:10px; width:300px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>At a local art workshop, a group of children is communicating with each other fluently without words</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Communication is a foundation of any business or organization.</strong>&nbsp;A team that communicates well will go further, and create more impact. Simple enough.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But there are so much to get in the way: busy schedules, pressure of a possible failure, and the lack of self-confidence, etc.. all contribute to fragmented, ineffective communications, where team members are lost, left with vague impressions, and stumble on and into each other.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ANAKOT and its team of trainers&mdash;a creative team with background in meditation, leadership and communication, innovation and design, acting and marketing&mdash;will teach you various activities and exercises that you can take back to your workplace to start communicating clearly,&nbsp;today. All&nbsp;without any lecture on the English grammar!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You will engage in&nbsp;<strong>hands-on, practical exercises</strong>&nbsp;designed to heighten the sense of your level of communication skills, and how you might work on improving them. You will&nbsp;<strong>learn your strengths and weaknesses,</strong>&nbsp;and how to take advantage of them in your communication with others. You will come away with a set of practices that you can easily continue on your own, and a set of resources to further your learning.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>LEARN HOW TO:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n\t<li><strong>Listen to your own sense of purpose,</strong>&nbsp;so your outward communication and messages&nbsp;will follow an authentic, natural voice of your own</li>\r\n\t<li><strong>Listen deeply to each other</strong>&nbsp;toward true understanding</li>\r\n\t<li><strong>Say&nbsp;&ldquo;Yes, and&hellip;,&rdquo;&nbsp;</strong>one of the most effective tools of communication, for creative&nbsp;collaboration and innovation</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>WHO SHOULD ATTEND:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li>leaders</li>\r\n\t<li>communication professionals</li>\r\n\t<li>managers</li>\r\n\t<li>program/project managers</li>\r\n\t<li>trainers</li>\r\n\t<li>&hellip;and anyone who wants to be more effective at his/her work!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>OUTLINE:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Module I:&nbsp;Finding Your&nbsp;Center</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n\t<li>Meditation as a way into your inner-purpose</li>\r\n\t<li>Knowing your values</li>\r\n\t<li>Vulnerability and authenticity</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Module II: Listening Deeply</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n\t<li>How do we listen? The Four Fields of Conversation</li>\r\n\t<li>Deep Listening exercises</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Module III:&nbsp;Impov: Creative and collaborative communication</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n\t<li>&ldquo;Yes, and&hellip;&rdquo;</li>\r\n\t<li>Storytelling</li>\r\n\t<li>Putting it all together</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>Please contact Chhunny if you want more information @&nbsp;<a href="mailto:chhuny@anakot.asia">chhunny@anakot.asia</a>&nbsp;| mobile : 078785044</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>ABOUT THE FACILITATORS:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="am-mug" src="/static/upload/201607221744344607.jpg" style="float:left; height:150px; margin:10px; width:150px" /><strong>Akira MORITA</strong>&nbsp;is a principal of Design Kompany, creative guru at Anakot and a listening enthusiast. He brings his thoughtful, design-centered ideas about work, creativity and collaborative innovation into the world of professional training.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://phnompenh.impacthub.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/163/2015/08/Chunny.jpg"><img alt="Chunny" src="/static/upload/201607221744535327.jpg" style="float:left; height:150px; margin:10px; width:150px" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Chhunny NOEM</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;has over twelve years of experience in leadership, management, group dynamics, public speaking, training and motivational speaking.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He prides himself on providing relevant and interactive learning forums where participants feel both comfortable to share, yet challenged to question their existing assumptions. Chhunny adds-value to participants&rsquo; learning by weaving personal wellness and balance into every training program he offers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Chhunny is a co-founder of Smallworld Cambodia, and a former co-Director of Possibilities World, a training company delivering Leadership Development and Management solutions. Chhunny has also delivered training workshops for clients in both the private and NGO sectors in leadership, management, soft skills and customer service. These clients include: a+b=3, 17 Triggers, Amansara Resort, Artisans D&rsquo;Angkor, Ucare Pharmacy, Shinta Mani Hotel, Soria Moria Hotel, Tara Angkor Hotel, Rambutan Resort, Clear Cambodia, ICS Asia, Phare Cambodia Circus, Young Startup Cambodia, CEFY project, Mlob Tapang and Farm to Table restaurant.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Chhunny taught meditation at the International Meditation Center of Chiang Mai for several years, incorporating the tenets of leadership and meditation as a guide for people on their quest towards effective self-empowerment, self-belief, and determination, and equipping them with the tools to create safe environments around them while committing to their life&rsquo;s passion.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Currently, he is a founding director of&nbsp;<a href="http://anakot.asia/" target="_blank">Anakot Asia</a>, a social enterprise that catalyzes the potential in human transformation and development through innovative training solutions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>WHERE:&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>SiSCO Cafe:&nbsp;</strong>Street 51 (Pasteur) &amp; Street 370</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>WHEN:&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>January 29, 1 &ndash; 5 PM</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>PRICE:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>$50 per person (includes refreshments, worksheets, a folder &amp; a certificate upon completion)</p>\r\n	data:image/jpeg;base64,	communication-for-success-a-four-hour-intensive-january-29-2016	2	1	1/2 Day 	50	SiSCO Cafe: Street 51 (Pasteur) &amp;amp; Street 370		2016-07-22 17:45:50.793963	2
